Peru Stocks: Ferreyros, Minsur, Relapasa, Siderperu, Telefonica

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-05-20T20:52:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/peru-stocks-ferreyros-minsur-relapasa-siderperu-telefonica.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index fell for the fourth day in five,
dropping 1 percent to 21,814.19. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index
declined 0.6 percent to 2,812.77.  Industrial stocks and utilities slumped as U.S. stocks fell
amid concern Greece will default on its debt, said Arlen Lahura,
a trader at Lima-based brokerage Coril SAB.  Telefonica del Peru SAA (TELEFBC1)  (TELEFBC1 PE), the local unit of
Telefonica SA, dropped 3.5 percent to 2.75 soles. Refineria la
Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Spain’s Repsol YPF SA known
as Relapasa, fell 3.2 percent to 1.80 soles.  Empresa Siderurgica
del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Gerdau SA known as
Siderperu, slid 3.2 percent to 1.52 soles.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1
PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer and a unit of Gloria SA, fell
1.9 percent to 15.70 soles.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the
Lima-based distributor for Caterpillar Inc., dropped 1.8 percent
to 3.30 soles.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, fell 1.3 percent to 3.95 soles after futures declined
in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
